review_blob:
Bottle 33. Appearance: muddy And impenetrable whit a heavy brown Head. Aroma: roasted coffee beans; liquorice and Light orange scent.
 Taste. Dark bitter chocolate, mocha coffee, roasted malt, whit long lasting flavor.
Bottle33. Aroma: Green Apple, some citrus. Flavor: fruit (Apple, white grapes), sweet, but not sickly, fresh, taste not long-lasting. An Easy Beer.
Bottle. Appearance: black black and black! Whit a thin beige head Aroma: burned coffee, liquorice, chocolate. Another one, please!!
Bottle. Appearance: Brown caramel whit a minimal beige head. Aroma: prunes, raisinis, smoky smell. Taste: viscous, a full-bodies flavour, burned sugar, some resinous.
beer_name: De Dochter van de Korenaar Embrasse

review_blob: Bottle. Blonde color, small white head. Nose: light smoked. Palate: medium smoked, slightly herbaceous and very balanced and so dangerously drinkable!!!

Bottle. Appearance: Dark brown whit light brown head. Nose: prunes and raisin, some alcoholic. Taste: mocha, roasted malty and some burned Sugar, dry in the final. Not a barley wine in my opinion, remember me a dark belgian stronge Ale.
Bottle. Pour amber whit a white head. Light sourness And bitterness, but well balanced, too balanced for my taste!!!!
I dont like the Weiss, but this one is inforgetalbe. Taste, some sweet, but Very balanced, whit Light banana, Spice, some Orange. Another one please!
Where is the aroma? Taste: Bitterness, but not so much, some Honey, but not so much, Very balanced, perfect for a warm day, but is not my favorite beer.

bottle. Beershop "mani in malto" Imola. Black body, Thin Brown Head. Aroma: coffee, roasty, dates and some alcohol. Flovour: licorice, espresso, bitter cocoa, but not perceived the fig and alcohol not completely covered.
beer_name: Mikkeller Crooked Moon Tattoo Stockholm Stout Brewed with Figs
